{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in the tactile regulation of Table 8, current studies on the tactile regulation of driver's emotions in CAVs mainly focus on temperature and vibration.",
    "Temperature regulation can be used to create a comfortable and calming environment in the vehicle.",
    "For example, heated or cooled seats can provide physical comfort to drivers and help them manage stress levels.",
    "Vibration regulation can also be used to regulate drivers' emotional states.",
    "For example, vibration of the steering wheel or seat can provide physical feedback to help drivers stay alert and manage stress levels.The study of temperature regulation by Schmidt et al. [154] reported that cool airstreams were associated with a decrease in low arousal and an increase in alertness and sympathetic activity, leading to better driving performance and acceptance."
  ]
}